 it, this book also examines how scripting is developing in the convergent media, beneath and beyond the Hollywood tentpole. By addressing specific genres across a wide range of media, this essential volume sets the standard for anyone in the expanded screenwriting industry and the scholars that study it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture authorship. 0aMotion picture plays. 0aScreenwriterszUnited States. 0aTelevision writerszUnited States. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Screenplays.2bisacsh1 aHoxter, Julian, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066755440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096104340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520961043423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520961043/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles